But the real miracle didn't become apparent

1343
01:01:15,970 --> 01:01:17,723
until the next racing season.

1344
01:01:19,410 --> 01:01:22,680
Michael's reputation brightened with every race he entered.

1345
01:01:22,680 --> 01:01:25,650
He displayed incredibly quick judgements and reactions

1346
01:01:25,650 --> 01:01:28,740
and his driving skills were a marvel to witness.

1347
01:01:28,740 --> 01:01:31,990
Out of 16 Formula One wold championships,

1348
01:01:31,990 --> 01:01:34,767
Michael had won 10, an unheard of record.

1349
01:01:34,767 --> 01:01:39,670
The nobody the previous season, he had become world famous.

1350
01:01:39,670 --> 01:01:42,030
His unexplainable transformation

1351
01:01:42,030 --> 01:01:45,000
caught the attention of Jo Carol Brane.

1352
01:01:45,000 --> 01:01:46,790
She wined him and dined him

1353
01:01:46,790 --> 01:01:50,570
and persuaded him to undergo a detailed examination.

1354
01:01:50,570 --> 01:01:52,810
We discovered that while he was driving,

1355
01:01:52,810 --> 01:01:54,640
Michael was secreting 10 times

1356
01:01:54,640 --> 01:01:56,980
the normal level of endorphins.

1357
01:01:56,980 --> 01:02:00,680
During my lab workup, I also discovered something else.

1358
01:02:00,680 --> 01:02:02,080
A grain of sand on which

1359
01:02:02,080 --> 01:02:04,820
some kind of mold or fungus was growing.

1360
01:02:04,820 --> 01:02:06,860
After intensive studies by our staff

1361
01:02:06,860 --> 01:02:09,020
of world renowned bacteriologists,

1362
01:02:09,020 --> 01:02:11,370
it was decided that this fungus just might be

1363
01:02:11,370 --> 01:02:14,220
the interacting agent we were looking for.

1364
01:02:14,220 --> 01:02:17,030
A search team equipped with state-of-the-art technology

1365
01:02:17,030 --> 01:02:19,270
was dispatched to the Serbian dessert.

1366
01:02:19,270 --> 01:02:20,690
They searched relentlessly.

1367
01:02:20,690 --> 01:02:23,322
Inch by inch, the sand was sifted and re-sifted.

1368
01:02:23,322 --> 01:02:26,620
Finally, they found the outcropping of the fungus.

1369
01:02:26,620 --> 01:02:29,000
We micro-analyzed it and devised a method

1370
01:02:29,000 --> 01:02:31,400
of refining and concentrating it.

1371
01:02:31,400 --> 01:02:34,040
A multimillion dollar refinery was constructed

1372
01:02:34,040 --> 01:02:37,190
for the soul purpose of producing Jo Carol's new product

1373
01:02:37,190 --> 01:02:39,870
which she had decided to call Endorph-A.

1374
01:02:39,870 --> 01:02:42,150
Naturally, the project was kept top-secret

1375
01:02:42,150 --> 01:02:45,303
until we had time to test and prove the new substance.

1376
01:02:46,783 --> 01:02:49,010
(sighing)

1377
01:02:49,010 --> 01:02:50,810
- And do you know how many volunteers you killed

1378
01:02:50,810 --> 01:02:54,020
during your campaign to test this artificial fungus?

1379
01:02:54,020 --> 01:02:56,210
- None of us knew about the virus!

1380
01:02:56,210 --> 01:02:57,380
We aren't monsters!

1381
01:02:57,380 --> 01:02:59,020
All of us were convinced we were working for

1382
01:02:59,020 --> 01:03:00,959
the benefit of mankind!

1383
01:03:00,959 --> 01:03:03,709
(waves sloshing)

1384
01:03:05,186 --> 01:03:07,436
(laughing)

1385
01:03:09,413 --> 01:03:10,246
- Jo, hi!

1386
01:03:11,260 --> 01:03:12,683
- Hi.

1387
01:03:12,683 --> 01:03:14,087
- Jo, you finally got here!

1388
01:03:14,087 --> 01:03:15,920
What took you so long?

1389
01:03:16,902 --> 01:03:18,103
(chuckling)

1390
01:03:18,103 --> 01:03:19,030
- Did you have a nice trip?

1391
01:03:19,030 --> 01:03:21,385
- Yes, it was very nice, thank you, Fendy.

1392
01:03:21,385 --> 01:03:24,322
(fireworks popping)

1393
01:03:24,322 --> 01:03:25,740
- Wow!

1394
01:03:25,740 --> 01:03:26,573
Golly!

1395
01:03:39,822 --> 01:03:42,405
(somber music)

1396
01:03:45,173 --> 01:03:46,793
I wish you were here, doctor.

1397
01:03:46,793 --> 01:03:48,404
I miss you.

1398
01:03:48,404 --> 01:03:50,571
(sobbing)

1399
01:03:52,900 --> 01:03:56,323
I'm having lots of fun but it's not the same without you.

1400
01:04:01,320 --> 01:04:02,340
- Is she asleep?

1401
01:04:02,340 --> 01:04:03,173
- Yes, ma'am.

1402
01:04:07,080 --> 01:04:08,610
I have new orders.

1403
01:04:08,610 --> 01:04:09,980
They came from the head office,

1404
01:04:09,980 --> 01:04:11,970
signed by the chairman personally.

1405
01:04:11,970 --> 01:04:13,524
- I understand.

1406
01:04:13,524 --> 01:04:16,274
(waves rumbling)

1407
01:04:17,752 --> 01:04:21,130
(wind howling)

1408
01:04:21,130 --> 01:04:23,630
You were always very helpful to me, Fendy.

1409
01:04:23,630 --> 01:04:25,500
I want you to know I appreciate it.

1410
01:04:25,500 --> 01:04:27,020
- This isn't easy for me.

1411
01:04:27,020 --> 01:04:28,890
I've been with you for 10 years.

1412
01:04:28,890 --> 01:04:29,990
As for little Pinoko,

1413
01:04:29,990 --> 01:04:32,270
I'm afraid that she and Dr. Black Jack are witnesses

1414
01:04:32,270 --> 01:04:33,833
and won't survive your mistake.

1415
01:04:35,376 --> 01:04:38,950
(gunshot booming)

1416
01:04:38,950 --> 01:04:40,300
I'm sorry, Jo, but our friendship

1417
01:04:40,300 --> 01:04:41,953
isn't as important as my job.

1418
01:04:43,983 --> 01:04:45,056
(gasping)

1419
01:04:45,056 --> 01:04:47,306
(groaning)

1420
01:04:51,480 --> 01:04:52,859
(gunshot booming)

1421
01:04:52,859 --> 01:04:55,900
(Fendy groaning)

1422
01:04:55,900 --> 01:04:58,103
- Sorry, Fendy, I still have work to do.

1423
01:05:00,900 --> 01:05:02,750
It's nothing personal, Fendy.

1424
01:05:02,750 --> 01:05:04,750
It's strictly business, pure and simple.

1425
01:05:06,077 --> 01:05:08,827
(dramatic music)

1426
01:05:11,127 --> 01:05:14,013
(boat horn blowing)

1427
01:05:14,013 --> 01:05:15,660
- [Pinoko] I wish Fendy could've come with us.

1428
01:05:15,660 --> 01:05:16,493
- [Jo] Me too.

1429
01:05:16,493 --> 01:05:18,180
She said to tell you she was sorry.

1430
01:05:18,180 --> 01:05:19,400
- What else did she say?

1431
01:05:19,400 --> 01:05:21,240
- Well, she said I shouldn't let you overeat

1432
01:05:21,240 --> 01:05:22,506
or watch too much television.

1433
01:05:22,506 --> 01:05:23,339
(giggling)

1434
01:05:23,339 --> 01:05:24,960
- [Pinoko] That's Fendy all right.

1435
01:05:24,960 --> 01:05:26,590
- When my mother was a little girl,

1436
01:05:26,590 --> 01:05:28,040
they didn't have television.

1437
01:05:28,040 --> 01:05:29,210
- Oh.

1438
01:05:29,210 --> 01:05:30,514
How awful.

1439
01:05:30,514 --> 01:05:34,014
(phone dial tone buzzing)

1440
01:05:35,330 --> 01:05:36,980
- [Operator] We're sorry, the number you have dialed

1441
01:05:36,980 --> 01:05:38,250
is no longer in service.

1442
01:05:38,250 --> 01:05:40,310
It was disconnected at the customer's request

1443
01:05:40,310 --> 01:05:42,010
and no new number has been listed.

1444
01:05:43,720 --> 01:05:44,683
- Thanks, Jo!

1445
01:05:45,600 --> 01:05:47,580
- [Man] Sorry, sir, they left no forwarding address

1446
01:05:47,580 --> 01:05:49,420
when they checked out.

1447
01:05:49,420 --> 01:05:50,310
- Thanks.

1448
01:05:50,310 --> 01:05:51,653
The fever's getting worse.

1449
01:05:52,650 --> 01:05:53,920
- I'm sorry they just vanished

1450
01:05:53,920 --> 01:05:55,190
off the face of the earth, doctor.

1451
01:05:55,190 --> 01:05:57,376
Nobody had any idea where to look for them.

1452
01:05:57,376 --> 01:06:00,209
(train whooshing)

1453
01:06:08,030 --> 01:06:09,557
- [Jack Voiceover] My temperature's been about 102

1454
01:06:09,557 --> 01:06:11,003
for the last three hours.

1455
01:06:12,160 --> 01:06:14,060
- [Eric] Are you sure you wanna go to the airport?

1456
01:06:14,060 --> 01:06:14,893
- Yes.

1457
01:06:17,350 --> 01:06:19,460
- [Jack Voiceover] I'm having to struggle to stay conscious.

1458
01:06:19,460 --> 01:06:21,263
I can't afford to become delirious.

1459
01:06:23,910 --> 01:06:26,040
I wonder what condition Jo Carol's in?

1460
01:06:26,040 --> 01:06:28,900
She drank a lot more of that Endorph-A than I did.

1461
01:06:28,900 --> 01:06:30,875
Is she able to care for Pinoko?

1462
01:06:30,875 --> 01:06:33,840
(waves rumbling)

1463
01:06:33,840 --> 01:06:36,660
- Get ready, world, here comes Pinoko!

1464
01:06:36,660 --> 01:06:39,420
Golly, I never felt so beautiful in my whole life.

1465
01:06:39,420 --> 01:06:40,380
I love it!

1466
01:06:40,380 --> 01:06:41,440
- I'm glad.

1467
01:06:41,440 --> 01:06:42,872
You are a beautiful girl.

1468
01:06:42,872 --> 01:06:44,690
- You're beautiful too, Jo.

1469
01:06:44,690 --> 01:06:46,250
Like a supermodel.

1470
01:06:46,250 --> 01:06:47,740
- Thank you very much.

1471
01:06:47,740 --> 01:06:48,573
- Beautiful lady,

1472
01:06:48,573 --> 01:06:50,969
may I have the honor of escorting you to dinner?

1473
01:06:50,969 --> 01:06:53,969
(upbeat jazz music)

1474
01:07:00,660 --> 01:07:01,760
Do you hear the band?

1475
01:07:01,760 --> 01:07:03,382
- [Jo] Be careful now!

1476
01:07:03,382 --> 01:07:04,215
- Hurry!

1477
01:07:04,215 --> 01:07:06,465
(groaning)

1478
01:07:07,730 --> 01:07:08,588
Jo?

1479
01:07:08,588 --> 01:07:10,046
(gasping)

1480
01:07:10,046 --> 01:07:10,879
What is it?

1481
01:07:10,879 --> 01:07:11,949
What's wrong?

1482
01:07:11,949 --> 01:07:12,866
Talk to me.

1483
01:07:14,529 --> 01:07:17,632
(whooshing)

1484
01:07:17,632 --> 01:07:20,460
- [Announcer] Flight 1533 will board in 10 minutes

1485
01:07:20,460 --> 01:07:21,668
at gate B7.

1486
01:07:21,668 --> 01:07:25,346
- Our flight will get you there three hours quicker.

1487
01:07:25,346 --> 01:07:28,346
(airport commotion)

1488
01:07:34,280 --> 01:07:35,910
- Doctor?

1489
01:07:35,910 --> 01:07:38,950
We found the files you wanted from the research center.

1490
01:07:38,950 --> 01:07:40,430
I can't believe how lucky we were.

1491
01:07:40,430 --> 01:07:43,700
It had fallen on the floor behind the shredding machine.

1492
01:07:43,700 --> 01:07:45,080
- [Black Jack] I knew they'd have tracking reports

1493
01:07:45,080 --> 01:07:45,913
on the victims.

1494
01:07:45,913 --> 01:07:49,100
(paper flipping)

1495
01:07:49,100 --> 01:07:51,763
Here's the final summary report on Lisa Siegel.

1496
01:07:53,120 --> 01:07:55,300
- [Man Voiceover] Since 1990, Lisa had been treated

1497
01:07:55,300 --> 01:07:58,790
at Parker Hospital for Paroxysmal Hemolytic Anemia.

1498
01:07:58,790 --> 01:08:02,180
In 1992, transfusion therapy was begun.

1499
01:08:02,180 --> 01:08:05,478
In 1994, experimental Endorph-A blood was added

1500
01:08:05,478 --> 01:08:07,900
by administrative order.

1501
01:08:07,900 --> 01:08:09,400
- [Jack Voiceover] Administrative order!

1502
01:08:09,400 --> 01:08:11,237
A business decision!

1503
01:08:11,237 --> 01:08:13,540
(plane whooshing)

1504
01:08:13,540 --> 01:08:14,860
- [Man Voiceover] In 1996,

1505
01:08:14,860 --> 01:08:17,360
she suffered Organ Insufficiency Syndrome,

1506
01:08:17,360 --> 01:08:20,770
all indication suggested probable blood stream infection.

1507
01:08:20,770 --> 01:08:23,408
In 1998, the patient expired.

1508
01:08:23,408 --> 01:08:26,040
(thunder rumbling)

1509
01:08:26,040 --> 01:08:28,110
Attending physicians were Michael Salon,

1510
01:08:28,110 --> 01:08:31,100
John Richardson, Judy Austin, Ralph Geiss

1511
01:08:31,100 --> 01:08:33,640
and on unofficial and confidential consultation,

1512
01:08:33,640 --> 01:08:36,030
and uncertified doctor, Kurō Hazama,

1513
01:08:36,030 --> 01:08:37,890
known as Black Jack.

1514
01:08:37,890 --> 01:08:40,070
For further information concerning the consultant,

1515
01:08:40,070 --> 01:08:43,331
Dr. Black Jack, refer to chief Dr. Jo Carol.

1516
01:08:43,331 --> 01:08:46,248
(thunder rumbling)

1517
01:08:50,062 --> 01:08:52,645
(wind howling)

1518
01:08:53,918 --> 01:08:56,751
(engine rumbling)

1519
01:08:59,000 --> 01:09:00,230
- My father was a Sybian.

1520
01:09:00,230 --> 01:09:02,040
This is like my second home.

1521
01:09:02,040 --> 01:09:03,230
This is Tonja,

1522
01:09:03,230 --> 01:09:05,133
the last outpost of civilization.

1523
01:09:06,710 --> 01:09:09,250
Beyond here, it's population zero.

1524
01:09:09,250 --> 01:09:11,580
The only humans you might see are nomadic desert people

1525
01:09:11,580 --> 01:09:13,473
who live constantly on the move.

1526
01:09:17,930 --> 01:09:20,423
See why that fungus was never discovered before?

1527
01:09:21,850 --> 01:09:23,980
Nobody in their right mind would come out here,

1528
01:09:23,980 --> 01:09:25,353
except the Desert Gods.

1529
01:09:25,353 --> 01:09:28,170
(somber beat music)

1530
01:09:28,170 --> 01:09:30,040
- [Black Jack] Who are the Desert Gods?

1531
01:09:30,040 --> 01:09:32,690
- That's what the villagers call the nomads.

1532
01:09:32,690 --> 01:09:35,360
Ordinary humans couldn't survive in such a place.

1533
01:09:35,360 --> 01:09:37,603
The nomads are a mysterious breed of people.

1534
01:09:39,550 --> 01:09:41,890
You'll never see them unless they want you to.

1535
01:09:41,890 --> 01:09:43,430
I have a feeling they're watching us

1536
01:09:43,430 --> 01:09:44,630
every minute we're here.

1537
01:09:45,519 --> 01:09:48,602
(ominous beat music)

1538
01:09:57,166 --> 01:09:59,749
(wind howling)

1539
01:10:07,510 --> 01:10:09,570
Brane's done a great job of disguising the place

1540
01:10:09,570 --> 01:10:10,640
as an oil refinery.

1541
01:10:10,640 --> 01:10:12,050
Pretty clever.

1542
01:10:12,050 --> 01:10:13,810
No one would ever suspect that what's actually

1543
01:10:13,810 --> 01:10:16,833
being refined here is a top secret pharmaceutical drug.

1544
01:10:19,550 --> 01:10:21,210
If you don't want anyone to know what you're up to,

1545
01:10:21,210 --> 01:10:23,875
there's no better place than here to do it.

1546
01:10:23,875 --> 01:10:27,340
(water whooshing)

1547
01:10:27,340 --> 01:10:29,293
Sounds like it's coming from the second level.

1548
01:10:36,250 --> 01:10:37,617
- Thank God.

1549
01:10:37,617 --> 01:10:39,035
- Huh?

1550
01:10:39,035 --> 01:10:40,605
- Pinoko!

1551
01:10:40,605 --> 01:10:41,550
- Is it?

1552
01:10:41,550 --> 01:10:43,466
Yes! Yes! It is!

1553
01:10:43,466 --> 01:10:44,756
It's...

1554
01:10:44,756 --> 01:10:45,867
It's our doctor!

1555
01:10:45,867 --> 01:10:46,700
- [Black Jack] Hey, it's all right.

1556
01:10:46,700 --> 01:10:47,632
- I thought I'd never see you again.

1557
01:10:47,632 --> 01:10:48,986
- [Black Jack] Everything's all right.

1558
01:10:48,986 --> 01:10:51,348
Don't cry, Pinoko, you're safe now.

1559
01:10:51,348 --> 01:10:52,230
There now.

1560
01:10:52,230 --> 01:10:53,563
There, there, it's okay.

1561
01:10:55,090 --> 01:10:56,420
What about Jo Carol?

1562
01:10:56,420 --> 01:10:58,580
Where is she, Pinoko?

1563
01:10:58,580 --> 01:10:59,830
- Jo's really sick, doctor.

1564
01:10:59,830 --> 01:11:01,591
She's got something awful.

1565
01:11:01,591 --> 01:11:03,758
(gasping)

1566
01:11:13,243 --> 01:11:14,124
Huh?

1567
01:11:14,124 --> 01:11:15,197
Stop that!

1568
01:11:15,197 --> 01:11:16,704
You shouldn't be trying to work.

1569
01:11:16,704 --> 01:11:19,454
Go back to bed, you need to rest.

1570
01:11:20,580 --> 01:11:22,340
- I don't have time to rest.

1571
01:11:22,340 --> 01:11:25,010
I have to find the answer before I die.

1572
01:11:25,010 --> 01:11:26,470
Can't give up.

1573
01:11:26,470 --> 01:11:28,183
Got to find the strength to go on.

1574
01:11:29,066 --> 01:11:31,316
(groaning)

1575
01:11:32,183 --> 01:11:33,310
(gasping)

1576
01:11:33,310 --> 01:11:35,610
- Still proud of this hideous monster of yours?

1577
01:11:35,610 --> 01:11:37,273
How does your own medicine taste?

1578
01:11:38,110 --> 01:11:40,610
- Have you reconsidered my offer to work together?

1579
01:11:41,850 --> 01:11:44,100
(laughing)

1580
01:11:45,590 --> 01:11:47,650
We'll find the cure for Moira

1581
01:11:47,650 --> 01:11:49,730
and we'll bask in the gratitude and worship

1582
01:11:49,730 --> 01:11:52,720
of millions all over the world!

1583
01:11:52,720 --> 01:11:54,450
But that will be nothing compared to the day

1584
01:11:54,450 --> 01:11:56,520
when mankind achieves its full potential

1585
01:11:56,520 --> 01:11:59,089
through the miracle of Endorph-A!

1586
01:11:59,089 --> 01:12:00,992
(gagging)

1587
01:12:00,992 --> 01:12:03,073
(blood squelching)

1588
01:12:03,073 --> 01:12:05,321
(coughing)

1589
01:12:05,321 --> 01:12:08,330
(whimpering)

1590
01:12:08,330 --> 01:12:09,860
- Stay there, both of you!

1591
01:12:09,860 --> 01:12:11,330
If you come in contact with her blood,

1592
01:12:11,330 --> 01:12:13,640
you could be infected too.

1593
01:12:13,640 --> 01:12:14,473
- What?

1594
01:12:14,473 --> 01:12:16,420
- Take Pinoko and get yourselves to a safe area.

1595
01:12:16,420 --> 01:12:18,810
Stay there until you hear further word from me.

1596
01:12:18,810 --> 01:12:19,910
- But doctor,

1597
01:12:19,910 --> 01:12:22,040
you're running a risk of being infected yourself.

1598
01:12:22,040 --> 01:12:23,520
Nobody's immune.

1599
01:12:23,520 --> 01:12:26,370
- I'm aware of that, Betty, but I've already been infected.

1600
01:12:26,370 --> 01:12:27,977
- But...

1601
01:12:27,977 --> 01:12:29,150
(gasping)

1602
01:12:29,150 --> 01:12:29,983
- Get out of here!

1603
01:12:29,983 --> 01:12:31,300
We have enough victims!

1604
01:12:31,300 --> 01:12:33,785
It won't serve any purpose for you to die too!

1605
01:12:33,785 --> 01:12:36,368
(wind howling)

1606
01:12:44,140 --> 01:12:45,120
- [Jack Voiceover] Are they expecting me

1607
01:12:45,120 --> 01:12:46,943
to perform some sort of miracle?

1608
01:12:54,982 --> 01:12:57,565
